{"http://www.concordia.ca/artsci/geography-planning-environment/news/archive/cunews/main/stories/2016/10/17/mtltrajet-an-app-with-street-smarts-travel-survey-zak-patterson.html": [["http://www.concordia.ca/content/shared/en/news/main/stories/2016/10/17/mtltrajet-an-app-with-street-smarts-travel-survey-zak-patterson.html", "\nHow often do you stop and think about how you get around the city every day?", "Concordia professor\u00a0", "\u00a0is teaming up with the City of Montreal to launch ", ", a mobile app that will help the city learn more about how its citizens navigate from point A to point B.", "\u201cI wanted to be able to undertake transportation and land-use research using emerging data sources,\u201d says Patterson, an associate professor of geography, planning and environment in the\u00a0", "\u00a0\u201cHowever, getting ahold of this kind of data proved difficult. So, using smartphones, I developed an app to collect my own data.\u201d", "The app initially launched as\u00a0", ", a 2014 pilot project. Close to 900 people downloaded the app, which prompted them to take part in a survey before it recorded their trips throughout the day using their smartphone.", "Developed at Concordia\u2019s\u00a0", ", the app asked users for information such as their purpose of travel and chosen mode of transport.", "\u201cIts purpose was to test how well we can use smartphones to collect travel data for transportation planning purposes,\u201d says Patterson.", "The app proved popular, and was used in studies as far away as Ghana. Closer to home, it will be used in five Canadian cities \u2014 Vancouver, Edmonton, Toronto, Montreal and Halifax \u2014 as part of this fall's\u00a0", ".", "The City of Montreal became interested when Patterson was a mentor at\u00a0", "\u00a0(MCC), an initiative designed to improve cycling in the city by using data sets to create urban mobility solutions.", "At MCC, Patterson discussed the DataMobile project with representatives from the city's transport department and the\u00a0", "\u00a0initiative.", "\u201cThe city is very enthusiastic about the adoption of new technologies in transport-related data collection,\u201d says Patterson. After he was invited to give a presentation on DataMobile for city officials, they asked him to use it as the basis of MTLTrajet.", "In advance of its October 17 launch, the app is already generating plenty of buzz, on the streets and at City Hall. \u201cIt has been great working with the city,\u201d says Patterson.\u00a0", "How will the results help advance Patterson\u2019s research?", "MTLTrajet will help Patterson and other researchers \u201cfigure out how to convert mere data to information.\u201d", "\u201cIt\u2019s a potentially effective tool because almost everyone carries around smartphones that know where they are, which can collect crucial transportation data,\u201d says Patterson.", "He emphasizes the app\u2019s data collection is transparent. \u201cThe process is completely overt, so that respondents will know what data is being collected from them.\u201d", "In the long term, Patterson\u2019s goal is to gather enough data to develop algorithms that will make it unnecessary to have any user input at all. Additional studies are already being planned by the University of Toronto, the\u00a0", "\u2019s Montreal office, the\u00a0", ",\u00a0", ", the\u00a0", "\u00a0and the\u00a0", "\u00a0A travel survey collection effort is also being developed in Lahore, Pakistan.", "So, if you\u2019ve spent your summer playing Pok\u00e9mon GO and are craving a new smartphone pastime while out and about, MTLTrajet may just be your new fall fix.", "\u201cThey both operate on smartphones and keep track of the location of the phone,\u201d admits Patterson. \u201cBut it is different, in that it's not a game \u2014 and uses less battery, I hope!\u201d", "\r\n        ", "\r\n    ", "\r\n        ", "\r\n    ", "Search for an expert to comment on any topic", "\u00a9 Concordia University"], ["Departm